These sources have been copied in from the official upstream drbd git repo at
https://github.com/LINBIT/drbd.git, after checking out drbd-9.0.24-1 and
updating submodules, by doing this:

% rm -v *
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/*.[ch] .
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/Kconfig .
% rm -v drbd_strings.c # which was a symlink
% rm -v lru_cache.c
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/linux/drbd*.h ../../../include/linux/
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/drbd-headers/drbd*.[ch] .
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/drbd-headers/linux/*.h ../../../include/linux/
% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/drbd-kernel-compat/drbd_wrappers.[ch] .

Also, make at toplevel of drbd tree should trigger generation of drbd/compat.h,
which we need to copy into our source tree to get drbd_wrappers working
propperly...

% cp -v /pathto/drbd/drbd/compat.h ../../../include/linux/drbd_compat.h

Then, since we renamed compat.h->drbd_compat.h, we have to sed some changes
into a few files:

% sed -i 's|#include "compat.h"|#include <linux/drbd_compat.h>|' \
      ../../../include/linux/drbd_config.h \
      ../../../include/linux/genl_magic_struct.h \
      drbd_int.h drbd_wrappers.h

And finally, we have to tweak a couple of include statements to work nicely now
that we've actually split headers out into their propper locations:

% sed -i 's|#include <kref_debug.h>|#include "kref_debug.h"|' \
      drbd_kref_debug.h

% sed -i 's|#include <drbd_transport.h>|#include "drbd_transport.h"|' \
      drbd_proc.c \
      drbd_transport.c \
      drbd_transport_tcp.c

% sed -i 's|#include <drbd_int.h>|#include "drbd_int.h"|' \
      drbd_transport.c

% sed -i 's|#include <drbd_protocol.h>|#include "drbd_protocol.h"|' \
      drbd_transport_tcp.c

Then generate drbd_buildtag.c w/ SHA of git tree.

Then modifying Makefile after reviewing diffs... and see if it compiles.  ;-)
If it doesn't, look in /pathto/drbd/drbd/drbd-kernel-compat/cocci for example
patches.
